docs.json: This file is used by notifications script, defines notification messages based on team performance states and conditions.

states.ok: OK: The team is doing great
states.mok: MORE OK: The team has been doing great for a while now
states.nok: NOT OK: The team is doing poorly
states.mnok: MORE NOT OK: The team has been doing poorly for a while now

log.message: Max of minimum number of states

obj.desc: When an issue is moved to In Progress, a branch associated to this issue must be created.
When an issue is moved to In Progress, a new branch associated to this issue must be created.
When an issue is moved to In Review, a Pull Request associated to that issue must be created.
When an issue is moved to Done, the Pull Request associated to the issue must be merged.
A developer should only be working on one issue at a time.
Each developer should be finishing at least 1 issue per week.
Most merged Pull Requests should have positive reviews.
Most of your merged PRs should be approved by your teammates.
If you merge a PR, it should be approved by at least 1 teammate.
You should comment or approve your teammates' PRs.
You should comment or approve at least one of your teammates' PRs in a week.
